Note:
DEPENDENCY SPEC - Package Dependency Source Primitive (Tier 1)

Implements a tagged DependencySpec record that parametrizes a single
dependency entry over its source kind. Mirrors the Cargo / npm / pip
union of dependency-source patterns:

  RegistrySource   ... name + version_constraint + registry_url
  GitSource        ... url + ref (branch/tag/commit)
  PathSource       ... local filesystem path
  ArchiveSource    ... url + sha256

Layout (DependencySpec record, 64 bytes):
  offset  0 : kind             (8 bytes, see DEP_* constants)
  offset  8 : name             (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset 16 : primary           (8 bytes, String pointer - url, path, or registry name)
  offset 24 : version_constraint (8 bytes, VersionConstraint pointer or 0)
  offset 32 : ref               (8 bytes, String pointer - git ref or 0)
  offset 40 : checksum          (8 bytes, String pointer - sha256 or 0)
  offset 48 : registry_url      (8 bytes, String pointer or 0)
  offset 56 : optional_flags    (8 bytes, bit field; bit 0 = optional, bit 1 = dev)

References:
  - Cargo manifest dependencies .... https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/specifying-dependencies.html
  - npm package.json dependencies .. https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v10/configuring-npm/package-json#dependencies
  - pyproject.toml dependencies .... https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/specifications/pyproject-toml/
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/version_constraint.runa" as VC

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let DEP_SIZE be 64

Let DEP_REGISTRY be 1
Let DEP_GIT be 2
Let DEP_PATH be 3
Let DEP_ARCHIVE be 4

Let DEP_FLAG_OPTIONAL be 1
Let DEP_FLAG_DEV be 2
Let DEP_FLAG_BUILD be 4

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a blank DependencySpec record with all fields zero. Callers use
the dedicated dep_init_* routines (one per kind) to populate it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 64 bytes and zero every field.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_create" returns Integer:
    Let d be proc allocate from Layout with DEP_SIZE
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 56, 0
    Return d
End Process

@Reasoning
Initialize a DependencySpec as a registry dependency. The constraint is
adopted (the spec releases it on destroy_deep); strings are caller-owned
pointers referenced by the spec but never freed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Populate kind, name, registry_url, version_constraint fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller is responsible for the lifetimes of the supplied strings.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_init_registry" takes d as Integer, name as Integer, registry_url as Integer, constraint as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 0, DEP_REGISTRY
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 8, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 16, registry_url
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 24, constraint
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 48, registry_url
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Initialize a DependencySpec as a git dependency.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Populate kind, name, primary (url), and ref fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller is responsible for the lifetimes of the supplied strings. The ref
should already be validated to a known commit / branch / tag form.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_init_git" takes d as Integer, name as Integer, url as Integer, ref as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 0, DEP_GIT
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 8, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 16, url
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 32, ref
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Initialize a DependencySpec as a local-path dependency.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Populate kind, name, and primary (path) fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Path traversal is the caller's responsibility - resolve canonical paths
before storing here.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_init_path" takes d as Integer, name as Integer, path as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 0, DEP_PATH
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 8, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 16, path
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Initialize a DependencySpec as an archive-URL dependency with mandatory
SHA-256 checksum. Per supply-chain best practice, archive sources MUST
carry an integrity hash so the lockfile pin survives upstream tampering.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Populate kind, name, primary (archive url), and checksum fields.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The checksum is the only defense against archive substitution attacks.
The dep_resolve / package-manager layer must verify it on download.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_init_archive" takes d as Integer, name as Integer, url as Integer, sha256 as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sha256 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cs_len be proc string_length from StringCore with sha256
    If cs_len is not equal to 64:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 0, DEP_ARCHIVE
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 8, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 16, url
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 40, sha256
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Toggle dev/optional/build dependency flags.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Bitwise OR into the flags slot.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_set_flag" takes d as Integer, flag as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 56
    Note: bitwise OR via addition when bits are non-overlapping
    Let cur_and be cur divided by flag
    Set cur_and to cur_and modulo by 2
    If cur_and is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 56, cur plus flag
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroy the DependencySpec record only; leaves all subordinate strings
and the VersionConstraint untouched.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not touch the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_destroy" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with d
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroy the DependencySpec and all subordinate string and constraint
allocations. Used by parsers that hold sole ownership of all referenced
buffers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Conditionally free each non-null subordinate; free the constraint via
the constraint_destroy_deep helper.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Double-free protection is caller's responsibility.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_destroy_deep" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 8
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name
    End If
    Let primary be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 16
    If primary is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with primary
    End If
    Let constraint be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 24
    If constraint is not equal to 0:
        proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with constraint
    End If
    Let ref be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 32
    If ref is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with ref
    End If
    Let checksum be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 40
    If checksum is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with checksum
    End If
    Let registry_url be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 48
    If registry_url is not equal to 0:
        If registry_url is not equal to primary:
            proc deallocate from Layout with registry_url
        End If
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with d
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: FIELD ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Expose the discriminator kind.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null - distinct from any valid DEP_* kind so callers can
detect error.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_kind" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the dependency name (the import-side identifier).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_name" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the primary source pointer - the registry name, git url, path,
or archive url depending on kind.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_primary" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the VersionConstraint pointer. Meaningful only for DEP_REGISTRY
dependencies; other kinds carry a non-version pin (commit, path, hash).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if absent.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_constraint" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the git ref (branch / tag / commit) for git-source deps.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 32.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if absent.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_ref" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 32
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the integrity hash for archive deps.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 40.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Callers verifying the hash must use a constant-time comparator from the
crypto module.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_checksum" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 40
End Process

@Reasoning
True if a specified dependency flag is set.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Bitwise AND test on the flag bit.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "dep_has_flag" takes d as Integer, flag as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 56
    Let q be cur divided by flag
    Let r be q modulo by 2
    Return r
End Process
